data.description: Nestled on 20 acres of serene landscapes, this secluded 3-bedroom, 2-bathroom home offers tranquil living with abundant natural beauty. Rock wood burning fireplace keeps the living space cozy for the cool Fall evenings.   Large basement with sump pump, laundry area and plenty of room for storage or workout area.  A wood burning stove with blowers is also in the basement.   A private pond graces the property, inviting peaceful reflections, while a shared pond further enhances the picturesque setting. Beyond the black metal gate, access the property via a shared driveway, leading to a charming residence adorned with spacious bedrooms and well-appointed baths. A shop with electric & water amenities provides a versatile space for hobbies or storage, complemented by a convenient chicken coop for poultry enthusiasts. Enjoy the harmonious blend of nature and comfort in this idyllic retreat, offering both privacy and the joys of rural living in Alma the Spinach Capital of the World! Selling as is where is.  AC unit is out on the HVAC system and sellers are offering a credit to the buyers in lieu of replacement. Portable AC/Heat unit is currently being used.
